rComments: I dreaded this class every single week, and, seeing as how attendance tripled every time we had a test, I assume everyone else did too. I didn't think anyone in the class liked him until I saw the comment below. He was just boring, scatterbrained, incomprehensible, and relied on far too many Simpsons references. In person though, a very nice guy.

Yes, he rambled in class, and his class structure was unorganized, but it was by far one of the best classes I've taken. This prof loves to teach, he has so much passion, you cant not like him.  He's very friendly, and he responds to email within 10 minutes, seriously.  I learnt so much from his class because it was non-conventional

Nobody, from slackers to keeners, liked his class. His lectures consist of him rambling and acting scatterbrained. There are dense readings but he offers little guidance or explanation about their relevance to the loose syllabus. I cannot stress this enough: do not take his classes.
